SIMPLE: horner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horner
<hw>Horn"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
works or deal in horn or horns.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who winds or blows the horn.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sherwood.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who horns or cuckolds.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Massinger.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The British sand lance or sand
eel (<spn>Ammodytes lanceolatus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hornet</ent>⟦br⟧
